package a26Looping_Statements;

public class aSample {
	
	/*
	 * adina descision chaiyatniki cheasea statements ni decision making statements antamu.
	 * adina looping chaiyatniki cheasea statements ni looping statements antamu.
	 */
	
	/*
	 * looping statements are the statements that execute one or more statement repeatedly
	   several no.of times.
	   
	 * Types of looping statements :
	   1. while
	   2. do-while
	   3. for
	   4. for each
		   
		   Syntax for while:
		   while(condition)
		   {
		   		//statements
		   }
		   
		   * while syntax is same as if syntax, daniki deniki difference entantea if 
		     only one time execute aavutadi and while matram multiple times work aavutadi.
		   
		   Syntax : it will execute postive outcomes
		   if(condition)
		   {
		   		//statements
		   }
		   
		   
		   Syntax for dowhile:
		   do
		   {
		   		//statements
		   }while(condition);
		   
		   * while ki do-while ki difference entantea :
		     1. while lo first conditions check cheasukoni tarvata statements execute chestamu.
		     2. do-while lo first ado vakati execute chestamu tarvata condition check chestamu.
		        do-while lo vaka special undi pass ina fail ina ado vakati ina do while matram 
		        vaka sari execute aavutundi.
	 */

}
